text: Faisal, Faisel, Fayçal or Faysal () is an Arabic given name. Faisal, Fayçal or Faysal may also refer to: ==People== * King Faisal (disambiguation) ** Faisal I of Iraq and Syria (1885–1933), leader during the Arab Revolt ** Faisal II of Iraq (1935–1958), last King of the Kingdom of Iraq ** Faisal of Saudi Arabia (1906–1975), third King of Saudi Arabia ==Places== * Faisal Cantonment, a cantonment town in Karachi, Pakistan * Faisal Colony, a neighbourhood of New Karachi Town in Karachi, Pakistan. * Faisal Equestrian Club, an equestrian club and restaurant in Gaza * Faisal Town, a residential area of Lahore * King Faisal Mosque (disambiguation) ** Faisal Mosque in Islamabad, Pakistan ** King Faisal Mosque, Sharjah, United Arab Emirates ==Other uses== * Faisal (film), a 2017 Indian film retitled Rubaai * Faysal Bank, a bank based in Pakistan == See also == * Fazal * Faisalabad, a city in Punjab, Pakistan Category:Arabic masculine given names fr:Fayçal
title: Faisal
